body:

We spent a long weekend in the Bay of Islands for Gemma's birthday and on one day we went for a run to Haruru Falls. 

![Mangroves](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/jqCHuKerQZiYvIeUyswDw92ytOk4lwIsfpjhzYzBPqnuGrbBUHNJzGyfJhKIVw0PDsHjaIXg7SyzrYuwBAy0_mqW22ycn5iFQv9oS-poS7GDRNov_NHdc3cMkbwMxC-Am4KXDVRvsw)

The way out was on a really nice trails through a forest and along a river.

![Haruru Waterfall](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/p-RNdwk6YUhyww9eZiaASAXPBNkpHv2t3A07heHGTYS7PXNuxcuKUV8Ttj2Mguh7is8HMEmRCVun88r5qjEPZvbztklrA6WUs9vjJ3ngfXVGUD-S_yo8F-muUNwmC7BoKzPBLLgNpQ)

At the waterfall we saw some chickens chasing each other around the car park.

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/khn2XO2By6A" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

After the waterfall we looped round on some gravel roads back to the start.

![Bay of Islands](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/01Px6uNZYNE7i-42XLIeUG3h30EFRrbEavfKQEKG2JVSRZUNMr7-wUWKUNySykT4QDAD2V4DYhTY0cTy9TRO4-C1GiB-q8qzoz5M__8e1gTHUwnIP-987jdh2vdFoSyjkQVHoD9vqQ)

